result.execSummary:
The defendant Nancy M Thao was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Failure to Support Child (120 Days+), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.22(2).
  • Failure to Support Child (120 Days+), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.22(2).
  • Failure to Support Child (120 Days+), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.22(2).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

]MK] case called at 9:34am.
Defendant Nancy M Thao in court, in custody, with Attorney Jeffrey De La Rosa.   ADA Brookellen Teuber appears for the State of Wisconsin. 
Maximum penalties recited; Constitutional rights reviewed; plea of " No Contest " entered on Counts #1, #2, and #3; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified (ADA Teuber submits the victim impact statement); the Court accepts the plea, finds the Defendant guilty, and orders Judgment of Conviction entered.

On Motion of the State, the Court reads-in and dismisses the remaining counts

The Court withholds sentence and places Ms. Thao on Probation for three years with conditions:
--to undergo assessment, treatment, or counseling as may be required by the Agent
--to obtain/maintain employment or education as directed by the Agent
--to comply with all Family Court Orders regarding child support
--to make all child support payments on time
--to make all payments on arrearages according to the Child Support orders
--to advise Child Support Enforcement Agency of any employment or address change within 48 hours of such change
--within five days of this sentencing-date or if confined, within five days of release, Ms. Thao is to report to the Child Support Enforcement Agency: Room 219 of the Jefferson County Courthouse, 311 S. Center Avenue in Jefferson WI, to complete a case management meeting 
--to comply with DNA sample provision
--not to leave Wisconsin without DOC approval
[--All payments toward child support and arrearages are to be paid through:  Wisconsin Support Collection Trust Fund, Box 74200, Milwaukee WI 53274-0200 (not through the Department of Corrections]
